      "message": "Just a suggestion for these steps:\n\nSince this test repeats the same keyword with different xpath/header pairs, we can move those pairs into a global list variable. That keeps the test shorter and makes future updates easier.\n\nFor example:\n\n#new tab links collection with format: xpath|header name\n@{new_tab_links}    //a[@href\u003d\u0027#/operations/firmware\u0027]|Firmware\n...                 //a[@href\u003d\"#/settings/network\"]|Network\n...                 //a[@href\u003d\u0027#/resource-management/power\u0027]|Power\n...                 //a[@href\u003d\"#/logs/event-logs\"]|Event logs\n...                 //a[@href\u003d\"#/hardware-status/inventory\"]|Inventory and LEDs\n...                 //a[@href\u003d\u0027#/logs/dumps\u0027]|Dumps\n\nThen the test case can be written as:\n\nVerify Overview Opens Link In New Tab\n    [Documentation]  Verify if hyperlinks open in a new tab.\n    [Tags]  Verify_Overview_Opens_Link_In_New_Tab\n\n    FOR  ${link}  IN  @{new_tab_links}\n        ${xpath_new_tab}\u003d  Fetch From Left  ${link}  |\n        ${header}\u003d  Fetch From Right  ${link}  |\n        Open Link In New Tab  ${xpath_new_tab}  ${header}\n    END",
